A GAP4 package for abstract algebraic algorithms in bacterial genomics.
The current implementation contains methods dealing with signed
permutations and several methods for calculating the word distance
in different group models.

If you use this package in your research please cite BioGAP as:

Attila Egri-Nagy, Andrew R. Francis, Volker Gebhardt, Bacterial Genomics and Computational Group Theory: The BioGAP Package for GAP, ICMS 2014, LNCS 8592, pp. 67–74, 2014.

